  "content": "* Open **QSTodoListViewController.m** and add the following method. Change _facebook_ to _microsoftaccount_, _twitter_, _google_, or _windowsazureactivedirectory_ if you're not using Facebook as your identity provider.\n\n```\n        - (void) loginAndGetData\n        {\n            MSClient *client = self.todoService.client;\n            if (client.currentUser != nil) {\n                return;\n            }\n\n            [client loginWithProvider:@\"facebook\" controller:self animated:YES completion:^(MSUser *user, NSError *error) {\n                [self refresh];\n            }];\n        }\n```\n\n* Replace `[self refresh]` in `viewDidLoad` with the following:\n\n```\n        [self loginAndGetData];\n```\n\n* Press  **Run** to start the app, and then log in. When you are logged in, you should be able to view the Todo list and make updates.\n"
